        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:45PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sheridan Lake, or 25 miles south of Cheyenne Wells, moving northeast
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sheridan Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
